CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 18, 1967, pg. 13 reads: "AKA's All - In observance of Founders Day, members of Alpha Kappa Alpha Sorority gathered at Stouffer's Restaurant in Oakland for lunch and a special recognition service. Here some of them are pictured looking pretty for Courier photographer "Teenie" Harris.  They are AKA's all."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Alpha Kappa Alpha members wearing dark dresses, most wearing hats, standing on staircase in Stouffers Restaurant for Founders Day celebration
